1. Convert equilibrated CHARMM structure to LAMMPS format
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   cd chm2lmp

   perl charmm2lammps.pl all27_msevb 1ots 92.390 92.390 235.544 > chm2lmp.log

   cd ..
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Inputs:  charmm2lammps.pl
            top_all27_msevb.rtf
            par_all27_msevb.par
            1ots.psf
            1ots.crd (1ots.pdb will be used if without 1ots.crd)

   Outputs: 1ots_ctrl.psf
            1ots_ctrl.pdb
            1ots.data
            1ots.in

2. Update LAMMPS *.data
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   cp chm2lmp/1ots.data .

   Update following sections in 1ots.data:
     1) Pair Coeffs    of water     HT  & OT
     2) Pair Coeffs    of hydronium HTH & OTH
     3) atomic charges of water     HT  & OT
     4) atomic charges of hydronium HTH & OTH
     5) Bond Coeffs section (especially reactive O-H bonds)
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3. Prepare evb.top
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   1st column: atom number


   2nd column: index of a reactive molecule/residue defined in evb.cfg

               1 --> hydronium,			H3O
               2 --> water,			H2O
               3 --> protonated   glutamate,	GL2-P
               4 --> deprotonated glutamate,	GL2-D


   3rd column: index of atoms in a reactive molecule/residue defined in evb_clc.par


   E.g., for hydronium here,
         1) in 1ots.data, the "Atoms" section
              200891   56700    54    -0.32     10.2694925768    20.6193300922      -9.92350959  # OTH
              200892   56700    55     0.44      9.7898955058    20.6891123353     -9.104160957  # HTH
              200893   56700    55     0.44      9.9473681087    19.8407787571   -10.4018720982  # HTH
              200894   56700    55     0.44     11.1813230773    20.4071821366    -9.6269342656  # HTH

         2) in evb.cfg
            settype H3O 1 : hydronium

         3) in evb_clc.par
            [molecule_type.start.H3O]

            :      HO        2
            :      |         |
            :      OH        1
            :     / \       / \
            :   HO   HO    3   4

            : number of atoms,   bonds,   angles,  dihedrals,   impropers,   starting rc
                          4        3        3         0           0          1
            : atomic information
            : atom type   charge   kernel
              OH          -0.32     1
              HO           0.44     1
              HO           0.44     1
              HO           0.44     1

         4) in evb.top
            200891 1 1
            200892 1 2
            200893 1 3
            200894 1 4
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------------

4. Prepare evb.type
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Atom/Bond/Angle/Dihedral/Improper   "names"     should match those defined in evb_clc.par
   Atom/Bond/Angle/Dihedral/Improper   "indeces"   should match those defined in 1ots.data

   E.g., for hydronium here,
         1) in evb.type
            : Atom Type
            #define OH 54
            #define HO 55

            : Bond Type
            #define OH-HO 87

            : Angle Type
            #define HO-OH-HO 184

         2) in evb_clc.par
            [molecule_type.start.H3O]

            :      HO        2
            :      |         |
            :      OH        1
            :     / \       / \
            :   HO   HO    3   4

            : number of atoms,   bonds,   angles,  dihedrals,   impropers,   starting rc
                          4        3        3         0           0          1
            : atomic information
            : atom type   charge   kernel
              OH          -0.32     1
              HO           0.44     1
              HO           0.44     1
              HO           0.44     1
            : bonds
            :  atom 1       atom 2      type
               1            2           OH-HO
               1            3           OH-HO
               1            4           OH-HO
            : angles
            :  atom 1       atom 2       atom 3     type
               2            1            3          HO-OH-HO
               2            1            4          HO-OH-HO
               3            1            4          HO-OH-HO

            : COC
            4
            1 2 3 4

            [molecule_type.end]

         3) in 1ots.data
            Masses
                  54    15.9994  # OTH
                  55      1.008  # HTH

            Bond Coeffs # hybrid
                  87      morse           79.086356      2.083387      0.98  # HTH  OTH

            Angle Coeffs # charmm
                 184         38.74335         111.7269                0                0  # HTH  OTH  HTH
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------------

5. Run MS-RMD simulations
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   sbatch msrmd.qsub

   Update "set stage = 1    # current stage" line to continue the simulation
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
